cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.CC

This paper is about differential privacy, which is a topic in computer security (cs.CR) and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the strength and composition of different variants of differential privacy, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper proposes a taxonomy of differential privacy definitions, which involves algorithms and complexity (cs.CC).
